    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 19</em>, <em>Rise of the Runelords Player's Guide pg. 11</em>, <em>Pathfinder Campaign Setting pg. 209</em>, <em>Inner Sea World Guide pg. 290</em>, <em>Adventurer's Armory pg. 0</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 24 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 10 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d8 (small), 1d10 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x3; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> P; <strong>Special</strong> trip</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Martial</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Polearms</p><h3>Description</h3><p>This large crook of sharpened metal makes it easy to trip and catch fleeing opponents. Invented by ogres, most ogre hooks are Large and crudely fashioned-often from metal torn from previous victims' weapons and armor. Despite their poor workmanship, the rarity and peril involved in getting ogre hooks make such items quite valuable.</p>"
